        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 1:30AM CDT by NWS Lubbock TX</headline>
        <description>At 130 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Hale Center, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Plainview, Abernathy, Hale Center, Petersburg, and Halfway.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
